That part which until 9.11.1896 formed parts of the parishes 
    of Compton Gifford, Egg Buckland, Laira Green and Pennycross. See also Table 2, note (c).

That part which until 9.11.1897 formed part of the parish of Plymstock. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Plympton St. Mary.

That part which until 9.11.1900 formed part of the parish of Weston Peverill. See 
    also Table 2, note (g).
Created 1894 out of the parishes of Ermington, Ugborough, Cornwood and Harford. See also Table 2, notes (b) and (h).

Abolished 9.11.1896 and divided between the parishes of Plymouth 
    and Plymstock. See also Table 2, note (c).
Created 1.4.1935 out of the parishes of Newton Ferrers, Revelstoke and Holberton. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parishe sof Newton & 
    Noss and Yealmpton.

Abolished 9.11.1898 and divided between the parishes of Devonport 
    and St. Budeaux. See also Table 2, notes (c) and (e).
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Newton & Noss.

That part which until 9.11.1896 formed parts of the parishes 
    of Compton Gifford, Egg Buckland, Laira Green and Pennycross. See also Table 2, note (c).

The part in Cornwall was transferred to Devon on 20.10.1844. See 
    also Table 2, notes (e), (f) and (h).

Created 1.10.1899 out of the parish of St. Budeaux. Abolished 
    1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of St. Budeaux and Compton Gifford. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).
